sql:
SELECT engagement_score
FROM event_analytics
ORDER BY engagement_score DESC;

external_knowledge:
- Average rating scores range from 1 (lowest) to 5 (highest); 
- A higher success rate indicates more successful event publications; 
- Event types may include conferences, seminars, workshops, among others; 
- User roles may include organizer, administrator, participant, etc.

- Average rating thresholds for rating categories: >= 4 is 'Highly Rated', >= 3 is 'Moderately Rated', and < 3 is 'Low Rated';
- Engagement metrics include attendance count and engagement score;
- Feedback is considered positive when the rating is 4 or higher.
